Business Analyst with Transaction Banking / Global Banking business-focused and end-to-end Transformation analysis experiences in the financial services or consulting environment.

Responsibilities :

Functional Analysis
Identify business needs (requirement gathering) – engage stakeholders (clients, users, mgmt., etc) to understand needs and translate them into specific requirements, backlogs and user journeys from design to testing;
Collect functional target from the stakeholders, understand, structure and enhance where applicable;
Collect functional information from stakeholders to feed these for technical integration;
Coordinate & challenge experts to put together a solution meeting business requirements, aligned on the target;
Leverage on Business Process Analyst to align the as-is on the target;
Formalize business requirements in user stories format;
Define clear action plan for the deliverable in charge & and ensure its execution by Functional Stakeholders;

Technical Analysis
Understand technical, integrations or development impacts of the functional objectives;
Anticipate and provide solutioning to technology challenges and provide stakeholders with structured functional information;
Coordinate, structure and ensure high quality deliveries of the technical specifications and user stories;
Take into account the execution of the cut-over plan between 2 systems i.e. establish parallel running, smooth decommissioning of old systems and eventual full cut over to new system.

Methodology, Reporting & Communication
Ensure agile methodology usage, define methodology & approach, document and present this prior to execution;
Identify technical & functional challenges, risks and issues, analyze them, document and escalate immediately to the Squad Lead;
Update the weekly project dashboard and action plan.

Requirements :-
Good understanding of corporate banking products especially trade finance;
Good verbal, written, reporting and stakeholders' management skills, able to interact appropriately with a variety of stakeholders, especially SMEs, front office, operations and IT teams;
Comfortable operating with a high level of autonomy;
Proven track record in implementing agile methodoology/ projects;
Experience in writing high quality user stories, functional specifications and technical specifications;
Strong analytical and problem solving skills, curious, with interest in deep diving into topics;
Good team working, collaboration and interpersonal skills;
Organized and delivery-focused, with attention to details;
Management consulting / Big4 Background is a plus;
Proficient in Microsoft Office (MS Word, Excel & Power point).

[What the role is]
Lecturer in School of Informatics & IT (Diploma in Big Data & Analytics)

[What you will be working on]
Conduct lessons and carry out all relevant responsibilities related to the teaching role in full time and part time course offerings in areas related to Data Analytics, Machine Learning, Data Engineering and Data Management and other foundational ICT modules.
Design, develop, maintain, and review course materials / curriculum as well as assessment. This involves making recommendations on areas of improvement that would enhance the students’ learning, performance and employability;
Develop student capabilities in project work (including e-learning and self-directed learning);
Coach and mentor students to support their learning;
Keep abreast with emerging trends in Big Data & Analytics technologies with active engagement with industry.
Support school’s initiatives through involvement in outreach programmes, committee work, projects and events.



[What we are looking for]
Relevant qualification in Information Technology, Computer Science, Business Analytics, Data Science or equivalent;
Minimum 2 years of relevant industry experience preferably in the fields of Data Science, Data Engineering, Data Warehousing, Data Management, Data Storytelling, Data Analytics, Machine Learning, Text Analytics;
Familiar with any of the following: Power BI, Tableau, R, Python, SQL, SAS, KNIME, RapidMiner, TIBCO, Alteryx, Cloud Technology like AWS/Azure;
Demonstrated ability in the application of Data Analytics/Data Engineering/Data Management/Machine Learning in real-world industrial settings with large scale data will be added advantage;
Passionate in technology and endeavour to learn new technical domains such as Artificial Intelligence and/or Machine Learning Ops;
Ability to work independently as well as in a team, and multi-task effectively;
Possesses passion and genuine interest to share knowledge and interact with youths and adults learners;
Good communication and interpersonal skills

